# AudioDemoSystem

## Purpose
Demonstrates the engine audio capability through the keyboard. Owns
`AudioDemoStateSingletonComponent` (created lazily on the first frame, tracking the music voice handle
and its play/pause state). Each frame it reads just-pressed keys and emits engine audio requests:
`S` plays the sample sound effect as a new overlapping voice; `M` toggles the looping music on/off; `P`
pauses or resumes the music. Returns early while the sandbox config or input state is absent.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SandboxConfigSingletonComponent | read | Sound/music clip UUIDs |
| InputStateSingletonComponent | read | Just-pressed key detection |
| AudioDemoStateSingletonComponent | write | Presence-check; created lazily; tracks the music voice |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| AudioDemoStateSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once; tracks music voice id + play/pause flags |
| PlayAudioRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted for sound effects and music start |
| StopAudioRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted to stop the music |
| PauseAudioRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted to pause the music |
| ResumeAudioRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted to resume the music |
